<p class="heading-desc t-justify">
<b>Designed to provide comprehensive CTD diagnostic insights and workflow efficiency</b></p>

<p class="heading-desc t-justify">
<b>Celiac Disease: A global challenge</b></p>


<p class="heading-desc t-justify">
Celiac disease is a chronic digestive and immune
disorder, found in genetically predisposed individuals, triggered by gluten ingestion, affecting the small intestine with a global prevalence of 1 in 1001. The diagnosis is often challenging due to a wide range of overlapping symptoms.</p>

<p class="heading-desc t-justify">
Current diagnostic tests include antibodies against <b>tTG</b>, <b>DGP</b>, as well as <b>Total IgA</b> and sometimes EMA (IFA). IgA is the isotope of choice, however, IgG is requested knowing the prevalence of Total IgA deficiency.</p>



<p class="heading-desc t-justify">

<b>Fast, Easy, Comprehensive</b></p>

<p class="heading-desc t-justify">

AliveDx planar microarray supporting celiac disease diagnosis, AiPlex CD, is designed to deliver rapid in-vitro test results, helping to reduce the time to results for patients. The panel combines both IgA and IgG, providing a comprehensive analysis in every sample.</p>

<p class="heading-desc t-justify">
<b>Designed to provide comprehensive CD diagnostic insights and workflow efficiency</b></p>

<p class="heading-desc t-justify">
AiPlex CD microarray contains key markers recommended by clinical guidelines American College of Gastroenterology (ACG) and the European Society for Paediatric Gastroenterology Hepatology and Nutrition (ESPGHAN) and the European Society for the Study of Coeliac Disease (ESsCD).
</p>

<p class="heading-desc t-justify">
Following guidelines (ESsCD), especially for pediatric population anti-tTG IgA results may help determine the need for an invasive procedure (no-biopsy diagnosis) based on the provided ULN (upper limit of normal). In case of IgA deficiency, testing for IgG autoantibodies are recommended.

</p>





