                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">
                            <span class="main-color"><b>ChondroHEAL</b></span> is a revolutionary concept in the field of regenerative medicine. The combination of an ultra-concentrated and ultra-filtered PRF, mixed with autologous thrombin, offers a new bioactive three-dimensional scaffold to use for cartilage defects and for tendon and ligament lesions. The benefits of having a slow release of growth factors over time (7 days) and the instant polymerization of the fibrin around the lesion, thanks to our delivery device, give surgeons a powerful tool for their practice.</p> 

                            <div class="panel-body fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">
                            <table>
                                <tbody><tr>
                                    <td class="width-40 "><i class="fa fa-crosshairs"></i></td>
                                    <td>IDRIA G is a PURE PRP with high concentrations of platelets and growth factors.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td class="width-40"><i class="fa fa-crosshairs"></i></td>
                                    <td>ProtSmart eliminates water from all the plasma of IDRIA G and concentrates cells, plasmatic proteins and fibrinogen.</td>
                                </tr>


                            </tbody></table>
                            </div> 


                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">
                            Starting from 28 ml of the plasma and cells produced by the 2 IDRIA G, Protsmart™ allows professionals to obtain in 5 ml of final product. A high concentration of cells, proteins and fibrinogen that reach a fourfold increase compared to the concentrations baseline in IDRIA G PRP.</p>
                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">When this compound is mixed through our mixing and delivery device with an autologous trombone produced by IDRIA S, it immediately becomes a stable scaffold with high tensile strength and adhesivity.</p>



                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 0; visibility: visible;">The method enhances tissue regeneration through site-specific release of cells whose growth factors act as a bridge for the new tissue.</p>



