                            <h4 class="panel-title">
                                <a role="button" class="" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#ChondroHEAL" href="#collapseOne16" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne16"><i class="fas fa-stream main-color"></i>ChondroHeal Preparation Process</a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseOne16" class="panel-collapse collapse fx animated bounceInRight" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="heading16">
                                        <div class="panel-body">
                                                <table class="margin-vertical-15">
                                                <tbody>
                                                    <tr>
                                                    <td class="width-40 "><i class="fa fa-crosshairs"></i></td>
                                                    <td><b>Blood collection:</b> The patient’s blood is drawn using a standard veneipuncture technique.</td>
                                                </tr>
                                                <tr>
                                                    <td class="width-40"><i class="fa fa-crosshairs"></i></td>
                                                    <td><b>Centrifugation and separation:</b> The collected blood is centrifuged to separate its components, including red blood cells, white blood cells, platelets, and plasma.</td>
                                                </tr>
                                                <tr>
                                                    <td class="width-40 "><i class="fa fa-crosshairs"></i></td>
                                                    <td><b>Plasma ultrafiltration:</b> The separated plasma undergoes ultrafiltration, a process that removes the water content and concentrates fibrinogen and other proteins. This results in a highly concentrated solution with potentially enhanced therapeutic effects.</td>
                                                </tr>
                                                <tr>
                                                    <td class="width-40 "><i class="fa fa-crosshairs"></i></td>
                                                    <td><b>Autologous thrombin preparation:</b> ChondroHeal utilizes autologous thrombin, derived from the patient’s own blood, instead of bovine thrombin. This reduces the risk of immune reactions and is advantageous for patients who have concerns about using animal-derived components.</td>
                                                </tr>

                                                <tr>
                                                    <td class="width-40 "><i class="fa fa-crosshairs"></i></td>
                                                    <td><b>Mixing and application: </b> The concentrated fibrinogen solution is mixed with autologous thrombin to create a fibrin gel, which can be applied directly to the treatment site to promote healing, tissue regeneration, and hemostasis.</td>
                                                </tr>

                                                </tbody></table>

                                                <p class="heading-desc t-justify">The use of plasma ultrafiltration in ChondroHeal offers an additional benefit. As it leads to a more concentrated preparation of fibrinogen and other proteins. This aims to enhance the therapeutic effects of the treatment. As the concentrated solution provides a higher amount of bioactive molecules to stimulate the healing and regenerative processes. As always, patients should consult with a healthcare professional before considering any experimental treatment options.</p>


