                                        <h3 class="heavy-font">
                                        Discover the power of iCCS that  stimulates the release of anti-inflammatory cytokines, providing pain relief, cartilage protection, and anti-aging benefits</h3>

                            </div>


                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">IDRIA S+ contains glass beads coated with positively charged ions. The interaction between beads and monocytes can stimulate the cells to release inflammatory mediators, such as the anti-inflammatory IL-1Ra. As well as increase the concentration of anti-inflammatory cytokines IL-4 and IL-10 without requiring an incubation period. Within 40 minutes, IDRIA S+ can process 30 ml of whole blood to produce 15 ml of autologous serum rich in cytokines. IDRIA S+ is combined with the ultrafiltrator Protsmart.</p> 
                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">By using the combination of IDRIA S+ and Protsmart 2 for a single treatment, it is possible to obtain a hyper-concentrated autologous serum rich in cytokines (Concentrated Autologous Conditioned Serum). The plasmatic water is eliminated, and the cytokines released from cells are concentrated.</p>
                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">Within the interleukin family, IL-1 is a pro-inflammatory cytokine released by immune cells during the early phases of inflammation. Its action can be regulated by IL-1Ra (interleukin-1 receptor antagonist), a naturally occurring cytokine released by monocytes. IL-1Ra binds to the IL-1 receptor, inhibiting the interaction between the receptor and the agonist, thereby preventing IL-1 intracellular signalling. IL-1Ra blocks the pro-inflammatory stimulus and promotes tissue regeneration.</p>


                                        <h3 class="heavy-font">
                                        Concentrated Autologous Conditioned Serum</h3>

                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">The combination of these two technologies allows the production of an enriched conditioned serum (Concentrated Autologous Conditioned Serum) without the need for incubation. Resulting in a substantial quantity of anti-inflammatory cytokines suitable for a single treatment.</p> 
                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">Injectable Concentrated Conditioned Serum (iCCS) is cell-free and abundant in anti-inflammatory cytokines and growth factors. This treatment provides anti-inflammatory, pain-relieving, cartilage-protecting effects, as well as anti-aging benefits.</p>
                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">Physicians can process 30 ml of blood and wait just 30 minutes for activation. Then obtain 15 ml of Injectable Concentrated Conditioned Serum with high concentrations of anti-inflammatory cytokines in a single 10-minute spin (2700 rgf). Afterwards, physicians can further process all serum components with ProtSmart 2 to achieve 5 ml of hyper-concentrated conditioned serum, enriched with proteins, growth factors, IL-1Ra, IL-4, and IL-10.</p>
                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">This process takes only a few minutes to be ready for direct injection into patients.</p>



