        <div class="panel-body">
             <p class="sub-heading t-justify">The Medicons is then inserted into the MediMax and the machine is started. The machine can be run from 10 seconds to 4 minutes depending upon the tissue type and the cell suspension you want. As the tissue is disaggregated, the cells pass through the screen into the suspension liquid in the bottom of the Medicons. Once the tissue is dissociated, the Medicons is removed from the MediMax 2.0. A needleless syringe is then inserted in the syringe port to recover the cell suspension. The Medicons may be rinsed with suspension buffer to ensure maximum cell recovery. Select the appropriate Filcons (or Filcons-Max if a 50 mL tube is used) pore size for isolation of the desired cells.</p>


