                                    <h3 class="heavy-font">
                                    Comfortable, Portable, and Powerful Recovery Technology</h3>

                        </div>

            <div class="list-item last-list fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">
                <label class="control-label"><i class="fa fa-align-justify label-icon"></i>Overview:</label>
                <p class="sub-heading">The <span class="main-color"><b>Revitalair® 430</b></span> is an advanced, low-pressure hyperbaric oxygen therapy (HBOT) chamber designed to deliver safe, effective, and comfortable treatment across a range of clinical and performance settings. Operating at 1.45 ATA, it provides optimal therapeutic pressure to enhance tissue oxygenation without the risks associated with higher-pressure systems. Its semi-rigid, zipper-free design incorporates a patented aluminum ring structure and ten transparent windows, offering both structural integrity and 360° visibility for a more relaxed patient experience. The chamber includes a removable stretcher, support table, and hypoallergenic internal padding, ensuring accessibility and comfort for users with varying mobility levels.<br><br></p>

                <p class="sub-heading">This state-of-the-art chamber is supported by BGS Hyperbaric Software, allowing healthcare providers to manage sessions, access training resources, monitor maintenance, and even connect through telemedicine. Built for safety, it features dual internal and external relief valves, rapid pressure cycles, and emergency depressurization capability. Whether in a sports recovery center, wellness clinic, or rehabilitation facility, the Revitalair® 430 combines clinical-grade performance with ease of use—making it a preferred solution for practitioners seeking reliable, portable, and scalable HBOT systems.<br><br></p>
                
            </div>

