    <h3 class="heavy-font">Rapid, Reliable Respiratory Results in One Hour.</h3>
</div>

<p class="heading-desc t-justify">
The <span class="main-color heavy-font font-20"><b>Respiratory Panel 1.1 (RP1.1)</b></span> by FlashDx is a user-friendly, fully enclosed multiplexed molecular assay designed for point-of-care settings. Utilizing a microfluidic cartridge preloaded with buffers and lyophilized reagents, it can detect and differentiate 13 key respiratory pathogens directly from nasopharyngeal, nasal, or throat swabs, whether collected in UTM, VTM, or saline media. With approximately 1 minute of hands-on time and a fully automated sample-to-answer workflow, it delivers results in under an hour.
</p>

<p class="heading-desc t-justify">
Powered by FlashDx’s proprietary semi-solid phase PCR (sSPRT) and microarray detection technology, RP1.1 provides high diagnostic accuracy. Clinical evaluations demonstrated excellent sensitivity and specificity across targets including SARS-CoV-2, Influenza A/B, RSV, adenovirus, parainfluenza viruses, rhinovirus/enterovirus, Mycoplasma pneumoniae, Bordetella pertussis, and human metapneumovirus. Its enclosed cartridge design, internal control for process integrity, and compatibility with random access testing make it ideal for decentralized healthcare and rapid respiratory diagnostics.
</p>

<div class="panel-body">
    <table>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="3"><span class="main-color heavy-font font-20"><b>Key Features</b></span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="width-40 center-bullet"><i class="fa-custom fa-circle font-8 main-color"></i></td>
                <td><b>Multiplex Capability</b></td>
                <td>Detects up to 13 respiratory pathogens including SARS-CoV-2, Influenza A/B, RSV</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="width-40 center-bullet"><i class="fa-custom fa-circle font-8 main-color"></i></td>
                <td><b>Sample Types</b></td>
                <td>Nasopharyngeal, nasal, or throat swabs (UTM, VTM, or saline)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="width-40 center-bullet"><i class="fa-custom fa-circle font-8 main-color"></i></td>
                <td><b>Hands-On Time</b></td>
                <td>Approximately 1 minute per run</td>
